    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nScrolling in a scrollable floating window with `C-e` and then scroll back with `C-y` until first line is shown and then trying to get top visible line of this window with `line('w0')` or `getwininfo().topline` will return `2` instead of `1` until you one more time scroll with `C-y` which will not scroll because topline already is `1`, but then `line('w0')` will correctly returns `1`. \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- Some minimal configuration with lsp enabled for lua files is required.\n- Open lua file and on some symbol (let it be `require` function) open and jump to hover documentation window with two `K`.\n- Scroll with `C-e` and `C-y`. One of each is enough.\n- execute `:echo line('w0')`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIn a floating window if first visible line is `1`, line('w0') should always returns `1`.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nHaven't tested\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR",
